(fn [f]
  ; the body of our higher order function is another function, as we want to manipulate the variables passed in our given function
  ; we return a list with a function and it's arguments to call the function
  (fn [arg1 arg2]
    ; the body of our inner function is a call to the function f, with the arguments reversed
    (f arg2 arg1)))
